Fabrizio Sestini - Senior Scientific Officer (FIRE, Future Internet=20=20
Research and Experimentation) at European Commission - From an=20=20
"Internet of the Future" to an "Internet FOR the Future"
  We are all aware how much the world has changed in the past 20 or 30=20=
=20
years. This transformation has brought about dramatic increases in=20=20
quality of life for a big part of its population, but at the same time=20=
=20
has made us aware of the existence of fudnamental limitations to an=20=20
indefinite growth. Future public priorities will have to be targeted=20=20
at achieving truly sustainable development, more sustainable economic=20=20
and financial models, more equally shared resources.
In this continuing transformation, it is clear that ICT technologies,=20=20
and Internet in particular, can and will play a major role. But how=20=20
so? Can we understand the link between technological developments and=20=20
social and economic transformations, so to predict and even anticipate=20=
=20
the impact of Technology on Society? Can we define a vision of the=20=20
future ICT-enabled world which is not driven by serendipitous=20=20
technology advancements but by desirable social goals?
This contribution will describe some of the activities currently=20=20
funded by DG INFSO in this area, notably a Study by the Oxford=20=20
Internet Institute which has identified some possible alternative=20=20
scenarios for a Future Internet and is exploring their implications,=20=20
especially for the future internet research priorities.

